{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-05-26T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Memorial Day honors the men and women who lost their lives while serving in the United States Armed Forces. Observed on the last Monday in May, the holiday traces its origins to the years following the Civil War, when communities began decorating the graves of fallen soldiers. Over time, it became a national observance dedicated to remembrance and gratitude—marked by solemn ceremonies, moments of silence, and visits to memorials across the country.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ArlingtonAmphitheater_EN-US0872772906_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ArlingtonAmphitheater_EN-US0872772906_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Where silence bears names","Title":"Memorial Amphitheater at Arlington National Cemetery, Arlington, Virginia","Copyright":"© idesignimages/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/38.883003,-77.068618/8?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=38.883003,-77.068618;S9;Arlington Memorial Amphitheater, Virginia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260525_ArlingtonAmphitheater\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Memorial+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260525_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260525_ArlingtonAmphitheater"},"Ssd":"20260525","Name":"ArlingtonAmphitheater","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"0872772906","FullDateString":"May 25, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The European Day of Parks celebrates protected areas across the continent, marking the creation of Europe's first national parks in 1909. It serves as a reminder that many of today's most iconic landscapes exist because of long-term conservation efforts. Today's image highlights a prime example of this legacy: Tre Cime Nature Park in northern Italy.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.DolomitesPark_EN-US0828472809_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.DolomitesPark_EN-US0828472809_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Preserving Europe's wild places","Title":"Tre Cime Nature Park, South Tyrol, Italy","Copyright":"© Adisorn Fineday Chutikunakorn/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/46.643931,12.343052/6?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=46.643931,12.343052;S9;Tre Cime Nature Park, Italy&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260524_DolomitesPark\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=European+Day+of+Parks&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260524_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260524_DolomitesPark"},"Ssd":"20260524","Name":"DolomitesPark","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"0828472809","FullDateString":"May 24, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Turtles are not only fascinating animals; they also play vital roles in nature. Sea turtles help keep seagrass beds and coral reefs healthy, while freshwater and land counterparts support balanced ecosystems. Their shells are part of their skeletons, formed from dozens of fused bones, and some species navigate using Earth's magnetic field to return to the beaches where they hatched.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ThreeTurtlesButterflies_EN-US0786859772_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ThreeTurtlesButterflies_EN-US0786859772_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Shell yeah, turtles!","Title":"Turtles with butterflies","Copyright":"© Patrick Gallet/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"There are seven species of marine turtles, and five are threatened with extinction.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260523_ThreeTurtlesButterflies\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Turtle+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260523_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260523_ThreeTurtlesButterflies"},"Ssd":"20260523","Name":"ThreeTurtlesButterflies","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"0786859772","FullDateString":"May 23, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Observed each year on May 22, International Day for Biological Diversity is a global reminder that life on Earth is richer—and more fragile—than it appears. Established by the United Nations, today highlights why protecting plants, animals, and ecosystems matters for food, medicine, climate stability, and everyday well-being.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.KauehiAtollLagoon_EN-US6299031230_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.KauehiAtollLagoon_EN-US6299031230_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":false},"Headline":"The shape of life at sea","Title":"Kauehi Atoll, Tuamotu Archipelago, French Polynesia","Copyright":"© WaterFrame_dpr/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-15.83333,-145.1167/5?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-15.83333,-145.1167;S9;Kauehi Atoll, Tuamotu Archipelago, French Polynesia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260522_KauehiAtollLagoon\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Day+for+Biological+Diversity&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260522_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260522_KauehiAtollLagoon"},"Ssd":"20260522","Name":"KauehiAtollLagoon","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"6299031230","FullDateString":"May 22, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"International Tea Day celebrates a drink that connects daily rituals to ancient landscapes. Just one look at the terraced tea fields of Sichuan Province, China, shows how deep those roots run. This misty region in southwest China is one of the earliest centers of tea culture, where people drank and cultivated tea more than 2,000 years ago. On nearby Mengding Mountain, a scholar named Wu Lizhen planted some of the world's first managed tea gardens during the Han Dynasty, laying the groundwork for generations of growers.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SichuanTea_EN-US0676754504_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SichuanTea_EN-US0676754504_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Brewing a legacy","Title":"Tea terraces in Sichuan Province, China","Copyright":"© lzf/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/30,103/5?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=30,103;S9;Sichuan, China&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260521_SichuanTea\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Tea+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260521_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260521_SichuanTea"},"Ssd":"20260521","Name":"SichuanTea","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"0676754504","FullDateString":"May 21, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"A soft buzz and a dusting of pollen can shape the future of our food. World Bee Day, observed each year on May 20, celebrates pollinators like the bumble bee pictured here during its quiet yet essential work. Unlike many insects, bumble bees use 'buzz pollination,' vibrating their flight muscles to shake pollen from flowers—a method vital for crops such as tomatoes, peppers, and blueberries.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BumbleBee_EN-US0634100541_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BumbleBee_EN-US0634100541_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Where the buzz begins","Title":"Bumble bee pollinating, Worcester, England","Copyright":"© SimonEastwood87/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Bees have five eyes—two large ones and three small ones in the middle of their head.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260520_BumbleBee\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Bee+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260520_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260520_BumbleBee"},"Ssd":"20260520","Name":"BumbleBee","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"0634100541","FullDateString":"May 20, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"At Mallorca's far northern tip, in Spain's Balearic Islands, the Formentor Lighthouse stands on the sheer cliffs of Cap de Formentor. This exposed headland is often called the 'Meeting of the Winds.' Built in 1863 and first lit on September 30 of that year, the lighthouse rises nearly 700 feet above the Mediterranean Sea and is reached by a narrow, switchback road about 8 miles from Port de Pollença. Under your feet is pale limestone—rock formed from ancient marine life and later lifted and carved by erosion into dramatic faces, sea caves, and natural arches. This rugged geology gives rise to the area's stark beauty and sense of isolation. Want to earn the view? Follow one of the peninsula's hiking routes, or tackle the short, steep climb to Talaia d'Albercutx for a watchtower panorama before continuing to the lighthouse. Keep an eye on the slopes: wild goats, descended from early domestic herds, spring across the ledges with effortless balance.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpainLighthouse_EN-US0598364035_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpainLighthouse_EN-US0598364035_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The edge of Mallorca","Title":"Formentor Lighthouse, Mallorca, Balearic Islands, Spain","Copyright":"© Allard Schager/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/39.96139,3.212222/5?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=39.96139,3.212222;S9;Formentor Lighthouse, Mallorca, Balearic Islands, Spain&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260519_SpainLighthouse\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Formentor+Lighthouse+Spain&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260519_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260519_SpainLighthouse"},"Ssd":"20260519","Name":"SpainLighthouse","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"0598364035","FullDateString":"May 19, 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Every June, Pride Month bursts into cities and streets across the United States—but its origins lie in defiance, not festivity. The observance grew from the Stonewall uprising of June 1969, when LGBTQIA+ New Yorkers pushed back against routine police raids, igniting a movement that reshaped civil rights history.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.RockefellerPride_EN-US1087499810_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.RockefellerPride_EN-US1087499810_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":false},"Headline":"Pride in plain sight","Title":"Rainbow flags at Rockefeller Center on June 28, 2020, New York City","Copyright":"© Noam Galai/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/40.758736,-73.978691/12?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=40.758736,-73.978691;S9;Rockefeller Center, New York&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260601_RockefellerPride\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Pride+Month+US&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260601_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260601_RockefellerPride"},"Ssd":"20260601","Name":"RockefellerPride","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"1087499810","FullDateString":"Jun 1, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today is the last day of American Wetlands Month, but don't let that bog you down. Take today to shine a spotlight on wetlands. Held throughout May, this national observance shines a spotlight on wetlands—some of the most productive ecosystems in the United States—and few places show their power quite like Everglades National Park. From above, Florida's iconic wetlands unfold as a vast patchwork of shallow water, sawgrass, mangroves, and winding channels, shaped by freshwater slowly flowing south from Lake Okeechobee.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.EvergladesWetlands_EN-US8572465847_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.EvergladesWetlands_EN-US8572465847_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Follow the flow","Title":"Aerial view of Everglades National Park, Florida","Copyright":"© Tetra Images/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/25.286623,-80.898659/7?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=25.286623,-80.898659;S9;Everglades National Park, Florida&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260531_EvergladesWetlands\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=American+Wetlands+Month&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260531_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260531_EvergladesWetlands"},"Ssd":"20260531","Name":"EvergladesWetlands","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"8572465847","FullDateString":"May 31, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Etosha National Park, Namibia, is not a place for soft starts, and the plains zebra foal in this image seems to get the memo. In a land this vast—nearly 8,600 square miles of salt pans and grassland—timing is everything, and hesitation is expensive. Lions, spotted hyenas, wild dogs, cheetahs, and leopards constantly pressure the herd—especially the youngest—so zebras are born ready. Minutes after arrival, they're upright. Hours later, they're moving.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.EquusQuagga_EN-US8240577582_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.EquusQuagga_EN-US8240577582_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Reading between the lines","Title":"Plains zebra foal in Etosha National Park, Namibia","Copyright":"© Sharon Heald/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-18.98073,15.762634/5?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-18.98073,15.762634;S9;Etosha National Park, Namibia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260530_EquusQuagga\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=plains+zebras&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260530_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260530_EquusQuagga"},"Ssd":"20260530","Name":"EquusQuagga","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"8240577582","FullDateString":"May 30, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"In Sagarmatha National Park, Nepal, Mount Everest rises into view, calm and unmoved as evening settles in. But on May 29, 1953, that stillness was broken. After years of planning and weeks of climbing, New Zealander Edmund Hillary and Sherpa mountaineer Tenzing Norgay reached the summit. At over 29,000 feet above sea level, they became the first people known to have stood at Earth's highest point.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SummitEverest_EN-US0552794971_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SummitEverest_EN-US0552794971_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A 'peak' into history","Title":"Mount Everest summit, Sagarmatha National Park, Nepal","Copyright":"© fotoVoyager/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/27.980471,86.880623/6?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=27.980471,86.880623;S9;Mount Everest, Sagarmatha National Park, Solukhumbu District, Nepal&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260529_SummitEverest\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Mt+Everest+summit+1953&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260529_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260529_SummitEverest"},"Ssd":"20260529","Name":"SummitEverest","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"0552794971","FullDateString":"May 29, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"As night settles over Suwon, South Korea, the old city wall pictured here shows that function doesn't necessarily cancel out beauty—it can create it. Built between 1794 and 1796 under King Jeongjo of the Joseon Dynasty, Hwaseong Fortress was more than a barrier. It was policy in stone: a reform minded push for a leaner, better-run state, driven by practicality and a deeply personal motive. Jeongjo ordered its construction to honor his father while strengthening a kingdom that wanted smarter systems, not just thicker walls.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.HwaesongFortress_EN-US1012626869_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.HwaesongFortress_EN-US1012626869_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Design meets discipline","Title":"Old city wall of Hwaseong Fortress, Suwon, South Korea","Copyright":"© aomam/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/37.289031,127.014114/5?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=37.289031,127.014114;S9;Hwaseong Fortress, Suwon, Gyeonggi, South Korea&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260528_HwaesongFortress\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=hwaseong+fortress+suwon&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260528_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260528_HwaesongFortress"},"Ssd":"20260528","Name":"HwaesongFortress","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"1012626869","FullDateString":"May 28, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"On World Otter Day, just look at this cutie swimming in the waters of Kachemak Bay, Alaska! Otters are captivating creatures that play an essential role in maintaining healthy ecosystems. Supported by the Otter Specialist Group (OSG)—a global network of professionals dedicated to the conservation of all 14 species—this day highlights the otter's vital contribution to nature. Known for their playful behavior and remarkable intelligence, otters are key indicators of waterway health. Sadly, they face growing challenges from habitat loss and pollution.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.OtterDay_EN-US0973120905_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.OtterDay_EN-US0973120905_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"No 'otter' like them","Title":"Sea otter, Kachemak Bay, Homer, Alaska","Copyright":"© roclwyr/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/59.725746,-151.141037/3?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=59.725746,-151.141037;S9;Kachemak Bay, Alaska&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260527_OtterDay\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+otter+day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260527_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260527_OtterDay"},"Ssd":"20260527","Name":"OtterDay","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"0973120905","FullDateString":"May 27, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"As spring sweeps across Northern California, the landscape is transformed by the vibrant displays of lupine flowers in shades of blue, purple, and white. Flourishing in the region's Mediterranean climate, these wildflowers provide a vital source of nectar for pollinators such as bees, butterflies, and beetles. With over 200 species found worldwide, lupines range from coastal varieties to those that thrive in mountain meadows. Beyond their striking beauty, lupines are essential to the ecosystem: by fixing nitrogen underground, they enrich soil fertility and support the growth of surrounding plants, even in nutrient-poor environments.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.LupineBloom_EN-US0920778137_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.LupineBloom_EN-US0920778137_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A season written in lupine","Title":"Lupine flowers in bloom, Northern California","Copyright":"© Jeffrey Lewis/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"The name 'lupine' comes from the Latin word 'lupus,' meaning 'wolf.' It was once incorrectly believed that lupines 'wolfed' or depleted nutrients from the soil.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260526_LupineBloom\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Lupinus&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260526_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260526_LupineBloom"},"Ssd":"20260526","Name":"LupineBloom","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"0920778137","FullDateString":"May 26, 2026"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"Image of the day","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"Learn more","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"Donate now","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"Quick fact:","LOC_HOMEPAGE_GALLERY_CARD_TITLE":"Recent Homepage images","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_GALLERY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Homepage image for {0}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_TITLE":"On this day in history","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"On this day in {0}, {1}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_SHARE_TOOLTIP":"Share today's Bing homepage","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERDOWNLOAD_TOOLTIP":"Download this image. Use of this image is restricted to wallpaper only.","LOC_MUSCARD_DOWNLOAD_LINK":"Download this image","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERNOTAVAILABLE":"This